    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2021-02-23</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2021-04-02T13:15:53Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Protecting Our Students and Taxpayers Act of 2021 or the POST Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill requires a for-profit institution of higher education (IHE), in order to participate in federal student-aid programs, to derive at least 15% of its revenue from sources other than federal funds. Current law requires a for-profit IHE to derive at least 10% of its revenue from sources other than federal funds.</p> <p>The bill also expands the definition of <i>federal funds</i> to include GI education benefits, with an exception for the monthly housing stipend provided under the Post-9/11 Educational Assistance Program.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
